  "root_text": {
    "an8.56:0.1": "Aṅguttara Nikāya 8.56 ",
    "an8.56:0.2": "6. Gotamīvagga ",
    "an8.56:0.3": "Bhayasutta ",
    "an8.56:1.1": "“‘Bhayan’ti, bhikkhave, kāmānametaṁ adhivacanaṁ. ",
    "an8.56:1.2": "‘Dukkhan’ti, bhikkhave, kāmānametaṁ adhivacanaṁ. ",
    "an8.56:1.3": "‘Rogo’ti, bhikkhave, kāmānametaṁ adhivacanaṁ. ",
    "an8.56:1.4": "‘Gaṇḍo’ti, bhikkhave, kāmānametaṁ adhivacanaṁ. ",
    "an8.56:1.5": "‘Sallan’ti, bhikkhave, kāmānametaṁ adhivacanaṁ. ",
    "an8.56:1.6": "‘Saṅgo’ti, bhikkhave, kāmānametaṁ adhivacanaṁ. ",
    "an8.56:1.7": "‘Paṅko’ti, bhikkhave, kāmānametaṁ adhivacanaṁ. ",
    "an8.56:1.8": "‘Gabbho’ti, bhikkhave, kāmānametaṁ adhivacanaṁ. ",
    "an8.56:1.9": "Kasmā ca, bhikkhave, ‘bhayan’ti kāmānametaṁ adhivacanaṁ? ",
    "an8.56:1.10": "Yasmā ca kāmarāgarattāyaṁ, bhikkhave, chandarāgavinibaddho diṭṭhadhammikāpi bhayā na parimuccati, samparāyikāpi bhayā na parimuccati, tasmā ‘bhayan’ti kāmānametaṁ adhivacanaṁ. ",
    "an8.56:1.11": "Kasmā ca, bhikkhave, ‘dukkhan’ti …pe… ",
    "an8.56:1.12": "‘rogo’ti … ",
    "an8.56:1.13": "‘gaṇḍo’ti … ",
    "an8.56:1.14": "‘sallan’ti … ",
    "an8.56:1.15": "‘saṅgo’ti … ",
    "an8.56:1.16": "‘paṅko’ti … ",
    "an8.56:1.17": "‘gabbho’ti kāmānametaṁ adhivacanaṁ? ",
    "an8.56:1.18": "Yasmā ca kāmarāgarattāyaṁ, bhikkhave, chandarāgavinibaddho diṭṭhadhammikāpi gabbhā na parimuccati, samparāyikāpi gabbhā na parimuccati, tasmā ‘gabbho’ti kāmānametaṁ adhivacanaṁ. ",
    "an8.56:2.1": "Bhayaṁ dukkhañca rogo ca, ",
    "an8.56:2.2": "gaṇḍo sallañca saṅgo ca; ",
    "an8.56:2.3": "Paṅko gabbho ca ubhayaṁ, ",
    "an8.56:2.4": "ete kāmā pavuccanti; ",
    "an8.56:2.5": "Yattha satto puthujjano. ",
    "an8.56:3.1": "Otiṇṇo sātarūpena, ",
    "an8.56:3.2": "puna gabbhāya gacchati; ",
    "an8.56:3.3": "Yato ca bhikkhu ātāpī, ",
    "an8.56:3.4": "sampajaññaṁ na riccati. ",
    "an8.56:4.1": "So imaṁ palipathaṁ duggaṁ, ",
    "an8.56:4.2": "atikkamma tathāvidho; ",
    "an8.56:4.3": "Pajaṁ jātijarūpetaṁ, ",
    "an8.56:4.4": "phandamānaṁ avekkhatī”ti. ",
    "an8.56:4.5": "Chaṭṭhaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "an8.56:0.1": "Numbered Discourses 8.56 ",
    "an8.56:0.2": "6. Gotamī ",
    "an8.56:0.3": "Danger ",
    "an8.56:1.1": "“Mendicants, ‘danger’ is a term for sensual pleasures. ",
    "an8.56:1.2": "‘Suffering’, ",
    "an8.56:1.3": "‘disease’, ",
    "an8.56:1.4": "‘boil’, ",
    "an8.56:1.5": "‘dart’, ",
    "an8.56:1.6": "‘chain’, ",
    "an8.56:1.7": "‘bog’, ",
    "an8.56:1.8": "and ‘womb’ are terms for sensual pleasures. ",
    "an8.56:1.9": "And why is ‘danger’ a term for sensual pleasures? ",
    "an8.56:1.10": "Someone who is besotted by sensual greed and shackled by lustful desire is not freed from dangers in this life or in lives to come. That is why ‘danger’ is a term for sensual pleasures. ",
    "an8.56:1.11": "And why are ‘suffering’, ",
    "an8.56:1.12": "‘disease’, ",
    "an8.56:1.13": "‘boil’, ",
    "an8.56:1.14": "‘dart’, ",
    "an8.56:1.15": "‘chain’, ",
    "an8.56:1.16": "‘bog’, ",
    "an8.56:1.17": "and ‘womb’ terms for sensual pleasures? ",
    "an8.56:1.18": "Someone who is besotted by sensual greed and shackled by lustful desire is not freed from wombs in this life or in lives to come. That is why ‘womb’ is a term for sensual pleasures. ",
    "an8.56:2.1": "Danger, suffering, and disease, ",
    "an8.56:2.2": "boil, dart, and chain, ",
    "an8.56:2.3": "and bogs and wombs both. ",
    "an8.56:2.4": "These describe the sensual pleasures ",
    "an8.56:2.5": "to which ordinary people are attached. ",
    "an8.56:3.1": "Swamped by things that seem pleasant, ",
    "an8.56:3.2": "you go to another womb. ",
    "an8.56:3.3": "But when a mendicant is keen, ",
    "an8.56:3.4": "and doesn’t forget awareness, ",
    "an8.56:4.1": "in this way that sort transcend ",
    "an8.56:4.2": "this grueling swamp. ",
    "an8.56:4.3": "They watch this population flounder, ",
    "an8.56:4.4": "fallen into rebirth and old age.” "
  },
